{"TopicId":210823,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How do I make parts \u0026quot;shiny\u0026quot;?","CreatedByName":"NerfTheVector_","CreatedById":223902,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-27T03:21:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"NerfTheVector_","CreatedById":223902,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-27T03:21:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo I\u0027ve been looking around at some KSP content lately, and I noticed that some creators made their parts \u0022shiny\u0022 (images below.) Is there a certain mod to do this, or is it a graphics option (my computer isn\u0027t great so I hope it\u0027s a mod.)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI also have ReStock and ReStock\u002B installed, I heard that does something?\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022suffering.png?width=1261\u0026amp;height=670\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002255.75\u0022 height=\u0022637\u0022 width=\u00221200\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/1032841607701069844/1043757153401438300/suffering.png?width=1261\u0026amp;height=670\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022unknown.png?width=691\u0026amp;height=670\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002296.96\u0022 height=\u0022670\u0022 width=\u0022691\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.discordapp.net/attachments/868936155599626251/1033873865262235748/unknown.png?width=691\u0026amp;height=670\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf anyone could help, that\u0027d be great! Thanks! \u003Cspan\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022:)\u0022 data-emoticon=\u0022\u0022 src=\u0022//kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/emoticons/default_k_smiley.gif\u0022 title=\u0022:)\u0022\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"jimmymcgoochie","CreatedById":199902,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-27T09:21:42Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI believe it\u2019s Magpie Mods that makes Restock/\u002B parts shiny, along with a variety of other mods\u2019 parts, and I think it uses TUFX to do so so you\u2019ll need both.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"HansAcker","CreatedById":195534,"CreatedDateTime":"2022-11-27T10:32:34Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf you want to get creative, have a look at TURD. It allows recoloring of most parts (and comes with shiny presets, too). I\u0027m not sure if it supports Restock, though.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022117203\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed1041280219\u0022 scrolling=\u0022no\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/index.php?/topic/174188-112x-textures-unlimited-recolour-depot/\u0026amp;do=embed\u0022 style=\u0022height:195px;max-width:500px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTo see it in action, you could watch one of my \u003Ca href=\u0022https://www.twitch.tv/jakeinaboat\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003Efavourite KSP streamers\u003C/a\u003E. He loves to Bob Ross all his creations.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}